2 Sec. 1. 23 V.S.A. § 607 is amended to read:
3 § 607. JUNIOR OPERATOR’S LICENSE
4 (a) A junior operator’s license may be issued initially only to persons who:
5 (1) are 16 and 17 years of age;
6 (2) have passed the driver examination required in subchapter 2 of this
7 chapter and a driver education and training course approved by the
8 Commissioner of Motor Vehicles and the Secretary of Education pursuant to
9 16 V.S.A. § 1044 or 1045; and
10 (3) have:
11 (A) possessed a learner’s permit for not less than one year;
12 (B) submitted on a form provided by the Department of Motor
13 Vehicles that is approved by the Commissioner, and certified by the operator’s
14 licensed parent or guardian, licensed or certified driver education instructor, or
15 licensed person at least 25 years of age that there was at least 40 hours of
16 practice behind the wheel, at least 10 of which was nighttime driving and that
17 the operator was accompanied by his or her the operator’s licensed parent or
18 guardian, a licensed or certified driver education instructor, or another licensed
19 individual at least 25 years of age, riding in the front passenger seat; and
20 (C) maintained a driving record without a learner’s permit
21 suspension, revocation, or recall for six consecutive months prior to licensure.
