2 Sec. 2. 16 V.S.A. chapter 23, subchapter 5 is amended to read:
3 Subchapter 5. Student Driver Education and Training Program
4 § 1044. DRIVER EDUCATION; HOME STUDY PROGRAM
5 (a) The Commissioner of Motor Vehicles and the Secretary of Education
6 shall approve one or more driver education and training courses, which shall
7 include a behind-the-wheel driver training component, suitable for a parent or
8 guardian of a high-school-age student enrolled in a home study program under
9 the provisions of section 166b of this title to use for teaching a home study
10 student.
11 (b) All driver education and training courses approved under this section
12 shall include:
13 (1) a course of instruction approved by the State Board on the effects of
14 alcohol and drugs on driving;
15 (2) instruction on motor vehicle liability insurance and the motor vehicle
16 financial responsibility laws of the State; and
17 (3) instruction on the adverse environmental, health, economic, and
18 other effects of unnecessary idling of motor vehicles and on the law governing
19 prohibited idling of motor vehicles.
20 (c) A course approved under this section may only be taught:
