1 Sec. 3. IMPLEMENTATION; REPORT
2 (a) The Commissioner of Motor Vehicles and the Secretary of Education
3 shall approve at least one driver education and training course pursuant to
4 16 V.S.A. § 1044 as added by Sec. 2 of this act not later than July 1, 2025.
5 (b) The Commissioner of Motor Vehicles shall gather aggregate data that
6 enables a written comparison of the driving records of operators who received
7 a junior operator’s license following participation in a driver education and
8 training course approved pursuant to 16 V.S.A. § 1044 with those who
9 received a junior operator’s license following participation in a driver
10 education and training course approved pursuant to 16 V.S.A. § 1045. The
11 Commissioner shall file the written comparison with the House and Senate
12 Committees on Education and on Transportation not later than November 15,
13 2029.
14 Sec. 4. EFFECTIVE DATE
15 This act shall take effect on passage.
